text: a small green corridor near the HDB, stretching from the hawker centre to the crossroad. small but lovely. the trees are tall and leafy, casting shadow for pedestrians. there are some benches to have a rest on, or just sit there watching the car flows or the sunset. scene is the most amazing at late afternoon, and very picturesque

just a small greenspace corridor at side of crossroads
a really nice spot to watch sunrise and sunset
sigh

A newly created cycling and jogging path for the local residents. It links all the block and the ECP connector. You could cycling passed petrol station for your ice cream on the way to the seaside. HDB is really putting a lot of nice thought in the design.
